#eNCA​ reporter Michael Appel takes a look back. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Ahmed Kathrada Foundation has weighed in on Former President Jacob Zuma's defiance of the State Capture Inquiry. It is welcoming the Inquiry's application to lay a contempt of court charge against Zuma. READ: State Capture Inquiry: Zuma no-show confirmed Zuma's recent actions are a contradiction in terms of a man who twice swore to uphold the Constitution. What's more, not so long ago, he was appealing to everyone to co-operate with the State Capture Inquiry. Watch the video above for the more details on this story.